rom\ncounter-streaming flows can be a source of in-situ transverse MHD waves, and\nthat for cool and dense prominence conditions such waves could have significant\namplitudes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 1 Jul 2018 21:25:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-25"}
